Jamaica Ave., south side, between 151st and 152nd Streets, showing in center of view a three story frame structure known as the Burdet house. Eugene L. Armbruster states that an individual named Golder conducted a feed store here. This source also gives as a resident, one Miller. Mrs. Jackson, wife of Dr. Oscar Jackson, was the last owner.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Jamaica Avenue, south side, between 151st and 152nd Streets, showing an old frame house in the center of the block, in rear of a brick building which fronts on Jamaica Avenue. The view is from 152nd Street, across a clearance. In the background is the Montgomery Ward building.

P. L. Sperr
